==Anglo-Saxon==

===Etymology===
*Derived from [[ǽwnian]] ''wv/t2'', ''to marry, wed''.  It is composed of [[be-]] and [[ǽwnian]], which is composed of [[ǽ]]w and the verb ending -nian.  It is ultimately derived from [[ǽ]].

===Verb===
'''beǽwnian'''

# to join in marriage, marry
*Type 2 weak transitive verb

===Pronunciation===
*be·ae:w·ni·an

